% Residual constraint reporting (BETA spec section 2.5).
% When a query reaches success with a non-empty constraint set
% whose members can be made true by some grounding, the runtime
% must print the remaining constraints and the binding, then ask
% whether to look for more solutions. Silently treating "constraint
% still has a free LV" as failure is a bug -- the engine has
% succeeded as far as proof search is concerned; the constraint is
% simply deferred.
%
% Expected for the query X > 5 (with X unbound):
%   The remaining constraints are:
%     X > 5
%   The binding is:
%   Find more solutions prompt, then yes.
